{"key":"processedPost-12413466","value":{"id":12413466,"first":12399300,"last":12426768,"when":1271598259,"utime":"04/18/10 04:44 PM","content":"Citric may have hit the nail on the head.&nbsp; Don't soak over 24 hours.&nbsp; Many endospore producing bacteria produce fresh endospores within hours after germination.&nbsp; By soaking long, you could end up with more bacterial endospores than you started with.&nbsp; Don't use the grains if they're rancid and stinking.<br /><br />Dry grains colonize much faster than wet ones.&nbsp; When I prep grains, they're so dry they almost rattle like rocks when shaken.&nbsp; However, a six pound spawn bag of rye colonizes in less than ten days.<br /><br />Another thing for the OP is to check your LC.&nbsp; That's more likely the problem than any mistakes you're making with the rye prep.<br />RR","title":"Re: SLOw/stalling colonizrion with rye grains, prep method?"}}